data.title: Daily Telegraph
data.meta_description: News and Breaking News Headlines Online including Latest News from Australia and the World. Read more News Headlines and Breaking News Stories at DailyTelegraph
data.text:
Fears Sydney underworld figure’s release will reignite tensions

NSW Police have moved to ensure a conflict that exploded in 2022 doesn’t reignite with the release of a major Sydney underworld figure from jail.

Aussie woman ‘gang raped in Paris’ days before Olympics

Police are investigating allegations an Australian woman was subjected to a horrific attack by a group of men in central Paris.

59 goals to 3: the trans side dominating women’s soccer league

The Flying Bats have five transgender players, scored an impressive 59 goals in the Premier League Women’s Division, conceding only three. But their latest 12-0 victory has some continuing to question their participation in female competition.

Ford vs. Wickham: Story behind one of swimming’s great mysteries revealed

One of Australian swimming’s longest and most divisive mysteries has finally been solved, almost half a century after the rumoured feud erupted between Tracey Wickham and Michelle Ford.

We wouldn’t pick a child rapist: Meares on Dutch controversy

Chef de mission Anna Meares has declared there would never be a spot on Australia’s Olympic team for a convicted child rapist, as the Dutch face increased scrutiny over the selection of Steven van de Velde.

Toughest selection battle ever gives Boomers winning edge

After a woeful World Cup in 2023 the Boomers are back and in the hunt for another medal at the Paris Olympics, says NBA star Josh Giddey.

‘I love you’: Mumbling Biden calls in to Harris campaign launch

Joe Biden has spoken for the first time since pulling out of the presidential race, as he prepares to return to the White House.

Why Obama won’t back Biden’s replacement

Former president Barack Obama’s failure to endorse Joe Biden’s pick of Kamala Harris as his successor points to a long and complex relationship between the two men, experts say.

TV host’s embarrassing Biden rant spectacularly backfires

A US TV host’s defence of Joe Biden has spectacularly backfired, but he’s not alone. But after today’s news, it’s all fallen apart, writes Tim Blair.

Two more men charged over Wakeley church riot

Police continue to make arrests 12 weeks after the Wakeley church riots, taking the total now charged to 39.

‘Full of sh*t’: Secret Service blasted over Trump shooting

Secret Service director Kimberly Cheatle was grilled by Congress after admitting the attempted assassination of Donald Trump was ‘the most significant operational failure’ in decades.

Affair sparked ‘very eastern suburbs’ blow-up: court

The matter of a Sydney recruitment professional assaulting her partner and colleague after he cheated on her before it was dismissed has been described as “very eastern suburbs” in court.

Utoikamanu decision looms after meeting with club for second time

The Stefano Utoikamanu transfer saga is expected to be resolved in the coming days, following news that the Tigers star met with the bosses of a powerhouse NRL club for the second time over the weekend. MARKET WATCH.

What’s driving hired gun to end Matildas’ 14-year drought

Tony Gustavsson has the reins of the biggest team in Australian sport, but few know much about him. He details the highs and lows of his journey with the Matildas, and the hurt driving them at Paris.

Does Meninga stick or twist with Tedesco Kangaroos captaincy?

James Tedesco’s loss of the NSW No.1 jersey has hurt his hopes of retaining the Kangaroos captaincy, leading to one of the biggest calls of Mal Meninga’s Test coaching career. DAVID RICCIO looks at the seven biggest stories still to play out this season.

Double blow for Blues star as Swan forward’s wings clipped

The Blues and Swans have taken a hit for their charge towards September, with two key players dealt massive injury blows. But there’s better news for Carlton on Harry McKay.

Buzz: Top 10 best buys of the 2024 NRL season

One started on a $1500 train-and-trial contract, another was axed from his previous two clubs. PHIL ROTHFIELD reveals his top 10 buys of the NRL season, with some names that you wouldn’t have expected at the start of 2024.

Boomers avoid injury disaster as Tokyo Patty Mills lands in France

The Boomers can breathe a sigh of relief as key man is cleared of injury after a thrilling Olympic warm-up win over France, with veteran star Patty Mills putting on a show.

Buckley’s chance: Giants sets Olympic record straight

After making headlines last week, GWS defender Jack Buckley has clarified his position on a potential journey to Paris to watch partner Celeste Mucci compete in the hurdles.

Man released on $20,000 bail after alleged stabbing

First class fail: Man accused of scaling airport fence to catch flight

Police say a passenger running late scaled a fence at a regional NSW airport in a bid to catch his flight – bypassing security. Here’s what we know.

‘Pool of blood’ kidnap case: Was it just boys ‘in a blue’?

Three of four alleged kidnappers remain in custody as a jury deliberates in a harrowing northern NSW kidnapping case. They will decide whether two blokes had a scuffle, or whether something more sinister took place.

War on the Homefront – NSW housing, rental crisis laid bare

Welcome to the biggest battle Sydneysiders are fighting in a generation. House prices surge in defiance of interest rate rises, the rental market spirals out of control, and fulltime workers live in tents in parks. This is The War on the Homefront docu-series.

Seventeen murders in two years. It is the worst gang war Sydney has seen in a generation. Watch every episode of The Daily Telegraph’s groundbreaking video series and delve into the tit-for-tat gangland killings that exploded into a family blood feud between the Hamzys and Alameddines.
